<article>
    <h1>Get fes&#xAD;tive at the air&#xAD;port</h1>
    <h2>Christ&#xAD;mas comes to Changi Air&#xAD;port, as the travel hub pulls out all the stops to cre&#xAD;ate a win&#xAD;ter won&#xAD;der&#xAD;land this Yule&#xAD;tide sea&#xAD;son</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201121/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-21"><time>2020-11-21</time></a>
        - <span>FRONT PAGE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Chan&#xAD;tal Sa&#xAD;jan&#xD;&#xA;Se&#xAD;nior Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent chan&#xAD;tal@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>It is be­gin­ning to look a lot like Christ­mas at Changi Air­port.</p>
    <p>The travel hub is tin­ker­ing with novel ways to en­gage visi­tors dur­ing and af­ter the pan­demic, and the yearend fes­tive sea­son is the per­fect time for it to give do­mes­tic tourism a much-needed shot in the arm.</p>
    <p>The air­port is trans­form­ing into a des­ti­na­tion in it­self, pulling out all the stops to cu­rate a soar­ing travel ex­pe­ri­ence with­out visi­tors even hav­ing to hop on a plane.</p>
    <p>At Ter­mi­nal 3 (T3), a freez­ing po­lar ex­pe­ri­ence is recre­ated at the Snow Hol­i­day sta­tion by Ja­pane­sein­spired life­style brand toki­doki.</p>
    <p>In­side the dou­ble-storey snow house that is kept at an Arc­tic mi­nus 10 deg C, visi­tors will hear their teeth chat­ter in a bliz­zard of foam snow, pow­ered by huge fans, while chil­dren ca­vort at slides made from packed snow.</p>
    <p>Then at T3’s de­par­ture hall, life-size di­nosaurs await at the Dino Wan­der­land sta­tion.</p>
    <p>At Jewel Changi Air­port, foam snow flakes fill the air at des­ig­nated spots on the ground floor near the HSBC Rain Vor­tex and at Canopy Park on the fifth and high­est level.</p>
    <p>From Nov 20 to Jan 3, those who have booked one of the more than 650 slots can have a stay­ca­tion at Shi­seido For­est Val­ley on ground level and at Cloud9 Pi­azza in glamp­ing tents.</p>
    <p>Mr Jayson Goh, Changi Air­port Group’s man­ag­ing di­rec­tor of air­port op­er­a­tions man­age­ment, says the group has or­gan­ised the Changi Fes­tive Vil­lage for a lim­ited pe­riod dur­ing the school hol­i­days to find out what would ap­peal to visi­tors.</p>
    <p>“De­pend­ing on the pub­lic’s re­sponse, we will then de­cide on how to de­sign fur­ther at­trac­tions or ac­tiv­i­ties to cater to their needs,” he adds.</p>
    <p>“We are de­lighted that our glamp-cation pack­ages are well re­ceived and have been taken up so quickly. We wanted to cre­ate a dif­fer­ent year-end ex­pe­ri­ence even as lo­cal res­i­dents are not yet able to travel, and lever­aged Changi and Jewel’s spe­cial ar­chi­tec­ture, in­te­rior to de­sign unique get­away experience­s that will ap­peal to our fans.”</p>

